msgctxt "sn47.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Sīlaṭṭhitivagga "
msgstr "3. Ethics and Duration "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 24. Suddhasutta → suddhakasuttaṃ (bj) | suddhaka (pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Suddhasutta "
msgstr "24. Plain Version "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.174, sc1
msgctxt "sn47.24:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.24:1.2"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, satipaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "sn47.24:1.3"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.24:1.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.24:1.5"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.24:1.6"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.24:1.7"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.24:1.8"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.24:1.9"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
